    "caption": "The stripey termite detective who works the day shift.",
    "shortDescription": "Numbats are tiny marsupials from Western Australia with rust-coloured fur and white stripes across their backs — perfect for vanishing into dappled forest shadow. Unlike most marsupials, they're out in full daylight, nose-down in rotting logs hunting termites. Fun fact: A numbat can flick its long sticky tongue in and out of a termite tunnel up to a hundred times per minute."
